{% assign breaking_blog_url = '/blogs/breaking-news' %}
{% assign archives_url = '/pages/archives' %}
{% assign submit_tip_url = '/pages/submit-a-tip' %}
{% assign about_url = '/pages/about-shadab-chow' %}
{% assign contact_url = '/pages/contact' %}
{% assign editorial_url = '/pages/editorial-standards' %}
{% assign corrections_url = '/pages/corrections-policy' %}
{% assign privacy_url = '/pages/privacy-policy' %}

<div class="newsroom-home">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <div class="hero-kicker">Independent publisher · Breaking news · Public accountability</div>
      <h1 class="hero-hed">Breaking news, crime coverage, corruption reporting, and public-interest accountability by Shadab Chow.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">A direct publisher homepage built to surface the mission, clarify what the site covers, and route readers quickly to reporting, trust pages, and tip submission.</p>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="{{ breaking_blog_url }}" class="btn btn-primary">Breaking News</a>
        <a href="{{ submit_tip_url }}" class="btn btn-secondary">Submit a Tip</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-panel">
      <div class="hero-panel__label">Publisher Focus</div>
      <ul class="hero-panel__list">
        <li>Independent reporting and verified updates</li>
        <li>Clear separation between facts, claims, and developing details</li>
        <li>Reader pathways to archives, standards, corrections, and contact</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mission">
    <div class="inner section-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="label">Mission</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">The site exists to document what happened, explain why it matters, and state plainly when key facts are still being verified.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="body-copy">
        <p>Coverage is centered on breaking developments, crime, corruption, public accountability, submitted evidence, and developing public-interest stories that need context instead of noise.</p>
        <p>It is a publisher platform, not a storefront. Readers should be able to move from the homepage into reporting, archives, editorial policies, and tip submission without digging through low-value filler.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="coverage">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="label">Coverage Areas</div>
      <div class="coverage-grid">
        <article class="coverage-card">
          <h3>Breaking News</h3>
          <p>Fast-moving stories, major developments, and timely updates with clear status labeling.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="coverage-card">
          <h3>Crime and Public Safety</h3>
          <p>Coverage that keeps allegations, arrests, and confirmed facts clearly separated.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="coverage-card">
          <h3>Corruption and Accountability</h3>
          <p>Reporting focused on misuse of power, public records, institutional failures, and scrutiny.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="coverage-card">
          <h3>Exclusive Footage and Tips</h3>
          <p>Reader-submitted documents, media, and leads reviewed for public-interest relevance.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="standards">
    <div class="inner section-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="label">Editorial Approach</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Independent reporting with trust signals that are easy to find.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="body-copy">
        <p>Readers should be able to reach editorial standards, corrections, privacy, and contact pages directly from the public homepage. That improves clarity for both audiences and policy review.</p>
        <div class="trust-links">
          <a href="{{ editorial_url }}">Editorial Standards</a>
          <a href="{{ corrections_url }}">Corrections Policy</a>
          <a href="{{ privacy_url }}">Privacy Policy</a>
          <a href="{{ contact_url }}">Contact</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-strip">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="label">Start Here</div>
      <div class="cta-grid">
        <a class="cta-card" href="{{ breaking_blog_url }}">
          <span class="cta-card__label">Read</span>
          <strong>Breaking News</strong>
          <span>Go straight to the primary reporting stream.</span>
        </a>
        <a class="cta-card" href="{{ breaking_blog_url }}">
          <span class="cta-card__label">Browse</span>
          <strong>All Stories</strong>
          <span>Find older coverage and topic history.</span>
        </a>
        <a class="cta-card" href="{{ submit_tip_url }}">
          <span class="cta-card__label">Send</span>
          <strong>Submit a Tip</strong>
          <span>Share documents, footage, and public-interest leads.</span>
        </a>
        <a class="cta-card" href="{{ about_url }}">
          <span class="cta-card__label">About</span>
          <strong>About Shadab Chow</strong>
          <span>Understand the site, mission, and editorial purpose.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
